link: https://coreos.com/os/docs/latest/generate-self-signed-certificates.html

== Consul server: ca_cert ca_config
1. start instance
2. local provisioner
   create certificate ${name}.internal.domain  ${ip} localhost 127.0.0.1 consul.r53.meteogroup.de  (server and client)
                      ${name}.internal.domain  ${ip} localhost 127.0.0.1 vault.r53.meteogroup.de   (server)
                      ${name}.internal.domain  ${ip} localhost 127.0.0.1 nomad.r53.meteogroup.de   (server and client)
3. remote provisioner
   cp certs and configs to final location
   restart consul
   restart vault
   restart nomad
   trust ca
      coreos:
      Copy the PEM-encoded certificate authority file (usually with a .pem file name extension) to /etc/ssl/certs
      Run the update-ca-certificates script to update the system bundle of Certificate Authorities. All programs running on the system will now trust the added CA.

